added.title: The Curse of Elmore
added.description: When Gumball's schoolfriend Leslie finds an old video tape, the creepy mystery of Elmore's ghostly past unfolds. Featuring spooky and hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

added.title: Elmore's Most Wanted
added.description: Gumball's dad has been revealed as "Elmore's Most Wanted" - but when the Chief of Police tries to investigate, things do not go according to plan. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

added.title: Mother's Day
added.description: Gumball, Darwin and Anais need to find the perfect Mother's Day gift. Will it be a cute card, a thoughtful painting or something entirely different? Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

added.title: Ancestor Act
added.description: When Gumball's sister Anais researches the Watterson family tree, she uncovers a long history of nonsense. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

added.title: The Magical Box
added.description: After Grizz, Panda and Ice Bear receive a special box, the brothers discover its magical ability to transport them anywhere in the universe.

added.title: Bears and the Beanstalk
added.description: The Bears work as short-order cooks in a giant's diner.

added.title: Boo-Dunnit
added.description: When the box goes missing at a haunted mansion, the Bears play detective to help uncover the thief.

added.title: The Little Mer-Bear
added.description: In order to live under the sea the Bears must transform into mermaids.

added.title: Modern-ish Stone Age Family
added.description: The Bears are invited to live with a family of cavemen but things get rocky when the bears teach the family about television.

added.title: Robo Teacher
added.description: When a substitute teacher fills in for Chef, Duncan thinks it's going to be the best day ever. He's wrong.

added.title: Glove Glove Me Do
added.description: Owen's newly found gloves make him great at everything. But this greatness comes at a high price.

added.title: The Tooth About Zombies
added.description: When Gwen's favorite event, the Zombie March, falls on the same day as Noah's nightmare event, dental hygienist check up day, Gwen and Noah find a way to help each other out.

added.title: Lie-Ranosaurus Wrecked
added.description: Owen pretends to be Izzy's pet dinosaur after leading her to believe she dug him up in the school playground.

added.title: An Egg-stremely Bad Idea
added.description: Hoping to 'brighten her day', Izzy and Owen pimp out Gwen's egg chair. But when it ends up in a museum run by angry chickens, they must retrieve it before Gwen destroys the daycare in a temper tantrum of unspeakable darkness.

added.title: #AdventuresInBunnysitting
added.description: Zee asks Kara to look after her two magical bunnies, which quickly start to multiply, wreaking havoc all across Metropolis.

added.title: #HateTriangle
added.description: When Hal's ex-girlfriend shows up at the Metropolis High homecoming game and goes love-ballistic as the villain Star Sapphire, Jessica begins to second-guess her own nonviolent tactics.

added.title: #BurritoBucket
added.description: Babs loves her job at fast food restaurant Burrito Bucket, but her boss, who's fed up with her chronic lateness and bad case of scatterbrain, would love any excuse to fire her. When a bank robbery breaks out right across the street from work, Babs is torn between her role as a superhero and dutiful Burrito Bucket employee. Will she be able to save the day and keep her job all in the nick of time?

added.title: #MeetTheCheetah
added.description: Barbara Minerva is super-jealous of  "little Miss Perfect" Diana Prince. But when she uses an ancient artifact from her dad's collection to place a curse on Diana, it turns out that Diana's not the one who's cursed. It's Barbara.

added.title: #Beeline
added.description: When she stumbles across a villainous plot to blow up a bridge, Bumblebee shies from the challenge of taking on the baddies and reaches out to her friends. But when the other heroes are all indisposed, it'll take every ounce of courage Bumblebee has to rise to the occasion … despite being the smallest of the bunch.

added.title: Game Over
added.description: Unagami breaks into the real world and terrorizes Ninjago City while Jay, Zane and Pixal attempt to prevent disaster by reuniting Unagami with his creator, Milton Dyer.

added.title: Shintaro
added.description: The ninja are invited to attend the birthday party of Princess Vania, in the distant Kingdom of Shintaro. They depart, bringing along Master Wu, unaware that he is feeling his age…

added.title: Into the Dark
added.description: When Cole investigates a mysterious visitor, the ninja aren't sure what to believe. Cole is frustrated with this lack of team support, until Princess Vania reveals a secret entrance that leads to an underground mine beneath Shintaro - where the city's dark secrets are held.

added.title: The Worst Rescue Ever
added.description: The ninja attempt to rescue Cole, but the bickering of his fellow prisoners, the Geckles and Munce, alerts the Skull Sorcerer, and soon the ninja are prisoners too.

added.title: The Two Blades
added.description: In order to escape the Skull Sorcerer's chain-gang, the ninja must convince the Munce and Geckles to put aside their distrust and work together… by promising them something they may not be able to deliver -- The Blades of Deliverance!

added.title: Shun and Lightning/Premonition of a Storm
added.description: Shun and Lightning: Shun and Lightning are on the hunt for a rare Tumpee, when they run into McQ! With all the devices related crimes happening in Los Volmos, Shun decides to investigate to try to get to the bottom of McQ's nefarious dealings./Premonition of a Storm: After a run in with McQ, Shun and Lightning find themselves in a little bit trouble. They're trapped!  Tied up with no Bakugan to help them escape, and no one knows their whereabouts. It will take some big help to help them get out of this mess.

added.title: Superstar Dan/Awesome Brawlers on Vacation
added.description: Superstar Dan: The Awesome Brawler's head to Tokyo for the Bakugan Battle League - Tokyo Edition. While Wynton, Shun, Lia and Lightning see the sites, and enjoy the tastes of Japan, Dan, as the Los Volmos Champion, has official Bakugan Battle League duties and obligations that keep him busy./Awesome Brawlers on Vacation: Lia, Lightning, Shun and Wynton explore the sights of Toyko when a rogue Bakugan shows up and rampages. The Awesome Brawlers have to spring into action, rolling out their Bakugan to stop the rogue enemy before any real damage can be done.

added.title: Bakugan Battle League, Tokyo Edition/Battle Royal
added.description: Bakugan Battle League, Tokyo Edition: It's the start of the Bakugan Battle League - Toyko edition! The first round will be a Battle Royale style competition, where only half the competitors will make it through to the next round. Along with the Awesome brawlers the field of competitors is filled with familiar friends and foes./Battle Royal: The first round of the Bakugan Battle League - Tokyo edition continues. The Awesome Brawler's and their Bakugan battle their way through the challenge and face off against tough competitors.

added.title: The Second Stage Begins/Mechanoids Attack!
added.description: The Second Stage Begins: With half of the brawlers eliminated, the second stage of the Bakugan Battle league begins. This round will be a timed race to the finish, with all kinds of tricks and traps that will slow down even the best brawlers./Mechanoids Attack!: Mechanoids have crashed the second stage of the Bakugan Battle League, causing all kinds of havoc. The Awesome Brawlers will now have to race against the clock, battling competitors and mechanoids if they want to make it through this round.

added.title: The Other Fight
added.description: Eliminated from the Bakugan Battle League, Ajit is airlifted by drone to a massive cargo ship in the middle of Tokyo Bay. Now that he's on board the cargo ship, he must rescue Dan and Drago, and stop whoever is sabotaging the Battle League. Dan and Ajit investigate the mysterious cargo ship that the eliminated brawlers and Bakugan are being held on. Dan races to track down Drago, but along the way runs into a familiar face.

added.title: Robo-Maestra
added.description: Cuando una maestra suplente reemplaza a Chef, Duncan cree que será el mejor día de la historia. Se equivoca.

added.title: Guantes, Guantes Maestros
added.description: Los nuevos guantes de Owen hacen que sea muy hábil en todo. Pero su grandeza tiene un precio.

added.title: Diente de Zombi
added.description: Cuando el evento favorito de Gwen, el Desfile de los Zombies, cae el mismo día que el día de pesadilla de Beth, la revisión con el dentista, las dos chicas encuentran un modo de ayudarse entre sí.

added.title: El Menti-Ranosaurio
added.description: Owen finge ser el dinosaurio mascota de Izzy después de hacerle creer que lo sacó del patio de la escuela.

added.title: Una Idea Huev-Xtremadamente Mala
added.description: Esperando "iluminar su día", Izzy y Owen decoran la silla huevo de Gwe. Pero cuando termina en un museo regentado por pollos rabiosos, deben rescatarla antes de que Gwen destruya la guardería en un berrinche de inusitada oscuridad.

added.title: Juego Terminado
added.description: Unagami entra al mundo real y aterroriza a la ciudad de Ninjago mientras Jay, Zane y Pixal intentan evitar el desastre reuniendo a Unagami con Dyer.

added.title: Shintaro
added.description: Los Ninjas están invitados a asistir a la fiesta de cumpleaños de la princesa Vania en la ciudad de Shintaro. Llevan al Maestro Wu que está deprimido.

added.title: En la Oscuridad
added.description: La princesa Vania revela una entrada secreta que conduce a una mina subterránea bajo Shintaro donde se guardan los oscuros secretos de la ciudad.

added.title: El Peor Rescate de la Historia
added.description: Los Ninjas intentan rescatar a Cole, pero las discusiones entre prisioneros alertan al Hechicero Calavera, y hace prisioneros a los otros Ninjas.

added.title: Las Dos Espadas
added.description: Para escapar de la prisión del Hechicero Calavera, los Ninjas debe convencer a los Munces y a Geckles de que dejen de discutir y trabajen juntos.

added.title: #LosConejosMágicos
added.description: Cuando Zee le pide a Kara que cuide a sus dos conejitos mágicos, pronto comienzan a multiplicarse y a desatar el caos por toda Metrópolis.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #TrianguloDeOdio
added.description: Cuando la exnovia de Hal aparece en el partido de bienvenida de la preparatoria Metrópolis y se enfurece por amor, convertida en la villana Star Sapphire, Jessica comienza a cuestionar sus propias tácticas no violentas.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #LaCubetaDeBurritos
added.description: A Babs le encanta su trabajo en el restaurante de comida rápida "La Cubeta de Burritos" , pero a su jefe, que está harto de que ella siempre llegue tarde y de su enorme dispersión, le encantaría encontrar cualquier excusa para despedirla. Cuando se produce un robo a un banco que está enfrente de su trabajo, Babs no puede decidir si encarnar su papel de superheroína o el de empleada obediente de La Cubeta. Pero ¿será capaz de salvar a todos y conservar su empleo justo a tiempo?
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #ConoceAGuepardo
added.description: Barbara Minerva está super celosa de la "pequeña señorita perfecta" Diana Prince. Pero cuando usa un antiguo artefacto de la colección de su padre para lanzar una maldición contra Diana, la maldición se vuelve en su contra.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #Beeline
added.description: Cuando tropieza con un malvado complot para hacer explotar un puente de la ciudad, Bumblebee se espanta y acude a sus amigas para que derroten a los malhechores. Pero cuando todas sus super amigas están ocupadas, Bumblebee debe buscar cada gramo de coraje en ella para hacer frente a la situación, a pesar de ser la más pequeña del grupo.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: The Wheel Deal
added.description: Everyone's excited about a grand bicycle outing through the park, everyone except Tweety whose little legs don't quite reach the pedals. Frustrated after riding on the back of Floyd's bicycle while everyone else has fun, Tweety is ready to go home.

added.title: Monster Mystery
added.description: Pocoyo makes a monster mask out of an old box. When he fails to scare Elly and Pato, he kicks the box out of the way in frustration. The box lands on Sleepy Bird who can't get out of it. She flies close to Pocoyo to ask for help but he and his friends are terrified. A chase ensues. Finally Baby Bird works it out. It was Sleepy Bird all along. The friends all have a monster mash party together at the end.

added.title: Poczilla
added.description: Pocoyo and Pato are playing at being terrifying giant monsters, like the sort of monsters they've seen in their comics. They find a toy city and enjoy being like Godzilla and King Kong. They don't notice that the little toys who live in the city are scared and that they're all running away in terror as Pocoyo and Pato destroy their toy city. The audience tells Pocoyo and Pato to stop. Once Pocoyo and Pato realize what's been going on they repair the damage and make a wonderful funfair for the little toys.

added.title: Elly on Ice
added.description: Pocoyo and Pato are having fun ice-skating. Elly is a great dancer and wants to have a go, but every time she tries she falls over flat on her bottom. Even Whale and Octopus put on a great duet ice-skating routine. Poor Elly is about to give up. But we encourage her to have another go, and Pocoyo and Pato help her to get started. Gradually she gets the hang of it and her confidence increases till she performs an amazing routine and achieves the highest score of the day.

added.title: Farewell Friends
added.description: Pato is leaving: he's packed his bags, he's said goodbye to his room and all his things. He's had one last sniff of his favorite flowers and said goodbye to Caterpillar, Alien, Baby Bird and Sleepy Bird. And there's the plane he's leaving in…! One last chance to say good bye. Good bye Pato!!! Everyone is waving and saying goodbye. Pato gets in the plane. One last wave. It's so sad!!! The plane goes in a circle one super-quick time and then Pato's home again. Hooray. Time for a welcome home party - and for someone else to have a go!

added.title: Double Trouble
added.description: Pocoyo wants to play ball but Pato is stubborn: he wants to play on the see-saw. Elly turns up so Pocoyo goes to play catch with her. Pato's left on his own. And the see-saw is no fun on your own. But he has an idea. He gets a machine and makes a copy of himself, a clone. The clone likes playing for a while but when they both want to play with the same toy car, they fall out. So Pato makes another Pato. Every time he makes a new Pato, something goes wrong, because the Patos all want the same thing and are as stubborn as each other. Finally, one of the clone Patos clones itself and soon there are crowds of Patos rampaging all around the place. Pocoyo and Elly to the rescue! They turn off the machine and all the copy Patos disappear. Phewy. To end, Pato plays ball.

added.title: Baby Brouhaha
added.description: Overhearing Granny on the phone say she's expecting a baby, Baby Bugs goes into overdrive, revving up the Baby Looney Tunes to prepare to care for an infant.

added.title: Flu the Coop
added.description: Baby Bugs and Baby Daffy decide to team up and unlike the other Baby Looney Tunes, fake having received their annual flu shots at the local clinic. The joke's on them when they awaken on the day of Granny's big party unable to have fun because they both have the flu.

added.title: Blast Off Bugs
added.description: Baby Bugs tries to realize his dream of traveling to the moon while the Baby Looney Tunes are on a space museum visit.

added.title: Oh Brother, Warehouse Art Thou?
added.description: Baby Sylvester is overcome with angst because Granny's broken old chair, his favorite napping place, must be replaced by a new, unfamiliar piece of furniture. The other Baby Looney Tunes work together to help turn Sylvester's trepidation into enjoyment during their mammoth furniture-shopping adventure.

added.title: Unlock the Magic: The Beginning
added.description: The discovery of an ancient, lost gateway leads the Care Bears on a rescue mission in the Silver Lining, a realm of natural wonders and comical creatures in the clouds beyond the borders of Care-A-Lot. While there, new discoveries expand the mission, challenging Cheer, Grumpy, and the mission team to grow beyond their present abilities and help the denizens of the Silver Lining.

added.title: A Patch of Perturbed Petunias
added.description: Share fears she's losing her ability as a problem-solver and peacemaker when she can't calm a squabble between a group of Whiffles and a flower bed of Perturbed Petunias. Cheer discovers it's not Share's fault; the Petunias are being secretly manipulated by Bluster's rumor-mongering.

added.title: Nobody's Perfect
added.description: When Cheer makes some simple mistakes, she begins to lose confidence in her piloting skills and herself. The self-doubt becomes so severe, she decides to step away from her role as pilot of the Cloudseeker. But the Team needs her, the Whiffles need her, and she must regain her self-confidence so they can stop Bluster's latest nefarious scheme.

added.title: A Yoorg Awakening
added.description: Funshine's jokes unwittingly hurt the feelings of a strange Rock Giant. Disturbed from its slumber, the usually benign creature inadvertently creates havoc for the Whiffles until Funshine calms it by apologizing.

added.title: Rain, Rain Go Away
added.description: After Grumpy's anger sends his belly badge out of control with a thunderstorm that floods a newly-planted Whiffle meadow, he vows to never be grumpy again. Renaming himself "Mr. Happy," he drives everyone crazy with niceness. When the Whiffles desperately need his clouds to make rain and Mr. Happy can't deliver, Cheer and the team must get him back in touch with his inner grump.

added.title: Picture Perfect Park Party/Sun Block
added.description: Hero Celebration Day is finishing with a slideshow of everyday heroes, that is, until the projector screen rips./Pretty Big City is cooling off with an ice slide in the park, but the situation gets slippery when the slide starts melting.

added.title: Tweety-Go-Round
added.description: Tweety leads The Looney Builders in building a new merry-go-round at the park for the kids. His crane breaks down and his small size affects his ability to contribute to the build.

added.title: Roll Chickens, Roll!/Ramp Up, Up, And Away
added.description: Farmer MacBarm is hosting the Sunny Field Farm Chicken Roll, but the race gets off to a slow start when the chickens don't roll./Ranger Nat can't wait to see Pinecone's Comet, that is, until his telescope falls to the bottom of a cliff.

added.title: Smash House
added.description: The Looney Builders learn that Taz accidentally destroyed his house, so they set out to build him a new one that's smash-proof.

added.title: Parking Lot
added.description: Bing's parking his speedy cars but what will Bing do when Charlie wants to play too?

added.title: Shadow
added.description: Bing is playing shadow tag with Flop, but what will happen when the clouds come?

added.title: Musical Statues
added.description: Bing gets to choose the game at Amma's Creche, but will his also be the winner?

added.title: Get Active Dance
added.description: Mei, Ella, animals and vegetables have a farm active day exercising and organising the farm

added.title: Voo Voo
added.description: It's breakfast time, and when Bing accidentally spills his Krispos, Voo Voo can help clean it up. But will that be all Voo Voo cleans up?

added.title: Garbage Truck
added.description: Blippi and TABBS shrink down and fly into a garbage truck where they meet Horace, a singing and dancing fly, who shows them what he loves to eat--garbage!

added.title: Salad Salsa
added.description: Mei, Ella, animals cook a delicious salad using local vegetables

added.title: Australia Kangaroo
added.description: Blippi stumbles across a Kangaroo Crossing sign in Australia and wonders "How high can a kangaroo jump?" His new kangaroo mate Rudy is happy to demonstrate, challenging Blippi to a hopping race around the famous sandstone monolith Uluru. Can Blippi jump as high as a kangaroo?

added.title: Here I Go
added.description: Bing and Pando find a new slide at the playground, but it's very high. Will Bing be able to go down the slide?

added.title: Prickly Pals/A Sting in the Tale/Tongue Twister
added.description: When Arlo plays too rough, Lucas forms a new friendship with a cactus./ Maizie accidentally stings Lucas's butt. This is a shock to them both, but Maizie takes it the hardest./ When Bodhi's tongue gets hurt, it's up to Dr. Lucas to help.

added.title: Sleeping Dogs/Skunked/Arlo And The Snake
added.description: Lucas and Findley discover a cake, and they try to keep Avocado asleep so everyone can have some./ Avocado gets skunked. Thankfully, Lucas helps her laugh at the situation./ Lucas has to convince Arlo that the garden hose isn't a snake.

added.title: The Adventurers
added.description: Because Mush-Mush, Chep and Lilit are always up to new adventures, Bolly has dubbed them The Adventurers. Flattered, our friends invite Bolly to choose his challenge to become an Adventurer too. Bolly will have to be the first Mushable to set foot somewhere. Mushton being crowded, Mush-Mush suggests they find an island, somewhere on the giant lake.

added.title: The Perfect Fritter
added.description: Chep has been watching Sushi-Mushi test new compost fritters recipes. When Mush-Mush gets to taste one, he can't believe it: Sushi-Mushi has cooked the perfect fritter. He tells the news to everyone in Mushton and now, all the Mushables want to taste the perfect fritter too! Only problem is the pressure is so high Sushi-Mushi can't remember the recipe anymore.
